					"body": "Titanium 3.1.1 currently does not use JSLint, nor will it ever. Titanium 3.2.0 uses UglifyJS and that will catch some syntax errors, though UglifyJS doesn't care about coding style. It's possible for someone to write a CLI plugin that runs JSLint, but that's outside the scope of Titanium.",
